gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 120, Wizards 99
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Wizards, 120-99. Jalen Brunson led the way with 32 points, seven rebounds, and seven assists for the Knicks, with Immanuel Quickley adding 27 points and six rebounds off the bench in the victory. Kyle Kuzma tallied 19 points, four rebounds, and five assists for the Wizards in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 1-1 in East Group B play, and 7-5 in the regular season, while the Wizards fall to 0-3 in East Group B play, and 2-10 in the regular season.
